Soldiers of 14 Brigade, Abia State have killed a robbery suspect said to be part of a five-member gang terrorising Aba, the stateâ€™s commercial city. Other members of the gang were arrested, one injured and taken to hospital, The Nation was told. The incident happened at an army outpost by the popular Ariaria Junction. A military source said the gang operating in a commercial bus refused to stop when the soldiers flagged them down, but instead barged into the military barrier. The soldiers sensing danger, opened fire on them, killing one and injuring another. Other members of the gang who tried to escape were arrested and handed over to the police. Locally-made pistols and 10 mobile phones were reportedly found on them.